    <exercise id="fs-id3255899" type="problem-exercises"><problem id="fs-id3255900"><para id="import-auto-id3158163">Two planets are on a collision course, heading directly towards each other at <m:math><m:semantics><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mn>0</m:mn><m:mtext>.</m:mtext><m:mtext>250</m:mtext><m:mi>c</m:mi></m:mrow></m:mrow><m:mrow/></m:mrow><m:annotation encoding="StarMath 5.0"> size 12{0 "." "250"c} {}</m:annotation></m:semantics></m:math>. A spaceship sent from one planet approaches the second at <m:math><m:semantics><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mn>0</m:mn><m:mtext>.</m:mtext><m:mtext>750</m:mtext><m:mi>c</m:mi></m:mrow></m:mrow><m:mrow/></m:mrow><m:annotation encoding="StarMath 5.0"> size 12{0 "." "750"c} {}</m:annotation></m:semantics></m:math> as seen by the second planet. What is the velocity of the ship relative to the first planet?</para>
